<% @js_modules = ['application'] %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-white relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Animated Background -->
  <canvas data-controller="particles" class="fixed inset-0 w-full h-full opacity-30"></canvas>
  
  <!-- Gradient Orbs -->
  <div class="fixed top-0 left-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-indigo-500/20 rounded-full blur-3xl animate-pulse"></div>
  <div class="fixed bottom-0 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-purple-500/20 rounded-full blur-3xl animate-pulse" style="animation-delay: 1s;"></div>

  <!-- Blog Post -->
  <article class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full">
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center text-slate-400 hover:text-indigo-400 mb-12 transition-colors group">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        Back to Blog
      </a>

      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Ruby</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Static Sites</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Web Development</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold mb-4 leading-tight">
          <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-400 to-purple-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
            Getting Started with Static Site Builders
          </span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg flex items-center">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 text-slate-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
          </svg>
          <%= Date.today.strftime('%B %d, %Y') %>
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
          <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Static site generators have revolutionised how we build websites. They offer the perfect balance between simplicity and power, allowing developers to create fast, secure, and maintainable sites without the overhead of traditional content management systems.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Why Static Sites?</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Static sites are pre-rendered HTML files that can be served directly from a CDN. This means lightning-fast load times, enhanced security with no server-side vulnerabilities, cost-effective hosting, version control friendly workflows, and easy deployment and scaling.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Choosing the Right Tool</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The static site builder landscape is diverse. From Jekyll and Hugo to custom Ruby solutions, each tool has its strengths. When choosing, consider your preferred programming language, template engine flexibility, build time and performance, community and ecosystem, and deployment options.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Getting Started</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Starting with a static site builder is straightforward. Most tools follow a similar pattern: install the generator, create your project structure, write your content in markdown or templates, then build and deploy. Whether you're building a personal blog, documentation site, or portfolio, static site generators provide a solid foundation for modern web development.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
